.TH "scsicam_bios_param" 9 "scsicam_bios_param" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scsicam_bios_param \- Determine geometry of a disk in cylinders/heads/sectors.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scsicam_bios_param
.BI "(struct block_device *bdev "  ","
.BI "sector_t capacity "  ","
.BI "int *ip "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bdev" 12
which device
.IP "capacity" 12
size of the disk in sectors
.IP "ip" 12
return value: ip[0]=heads, ip[1]=sectors, ip[2]=cylinders
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
determine the BIOS mapping/geometry used for a drive in a
SCSI-CAM system, storing the results in ip as required
by the HDIO_GETGEO \fBioctl\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
-1 on failure, 0 on success.
